      "en": {
        "name": "Respiratory rate (RR)",
        "category": "Vital signs",
        "subcategory": "Ventilatory",
        "shortDescription": "Respiratory rate (RR) — breaths per minute (/min); the measured rate (any method, incl. on the ventilator) and the ventilator set rate.",
        "longDescription": "## Definition & Clinical Context\n\nRespiratory rate (RR) is the number of breaths per minute — a core vital sign and ventilation parameter. In source data it is a single numeric value per patient-timestamp, measured by any means (bedside count, monitor impedance, capnography, pulse oximetry, the ventilator, etc.) or set on the ventilator. It is recorded across intensive care, anaesthesia, wards and emergency settings. It is reported in breaths per minute (UCUM unit /min). The measurement method and the set-vs-measured distinction are attributes of the value, not separate variables, so they are grouped in this single set.\n\n## Included Concepts\n\nThe set groups the SNOMED and LOINC respiratory-rate concepts (a single `respiratory_rate` variable). They are organised below by source/context for readability only — all are part of the same set, all in /min.\n\n### Generic respiratory rate (default)\n\n- *3024171 / 9279-1 — Respiratory rate (LOINC)* and *4313591 / 86290005 — Respiratory rate (SNOMED)*: the default.\n- *4108446 / 250810003 — Total breath rate (SNOMED)*, *4154772 / 271625008 — Rate of spontaneous respiration (SNOMED)*, *45770405 / 927961000000102 — Baseline respiratory rate (SNOMED)*, *1175625 / 76528-9 — Breath rate spontaneous (LOINC)*.\n\n### Measured on the ventilator\n\n- *3007646 / 19840-8 — Breath rate spontaneous and mechanical --on ventilator (LOINC)*: total measured rate.\n- *3026892 / 19839-0 — Breath rate spontaneous --on ventilator (LOINC)*: spontaneous component.\n\n### Ventilator set rate\n\n- *3007469 / 19834-1 — Breath rate setting Ventilator (LOINC)*: the rate set on the ventilator.\n\n### By measurement method\n\n- *21490867 / 76270-8 — Respiratory rate by Impedance.transthoracic (LOINC)*, *42527123 / 76174-2 — Respiratory rate by Pulse oximetry.plethysmograph (LOINC)*, *21490847 / 76172-6 — Respiratory rate by Carbon dioxide measurement (LOINC)*, *21490846 / 76171-8 — Respiratory rate by Airway flow measurement (LOINC)*, *21490845 / 76170-0 — Respiratory rate by Acoustic measurement (LOINC)*, *36303374 / 76173-4 — Respiratory rate by Non-airway pressure measurement (LOINC)*, *3006396 / 19841-6 — Respiratory rate by Spirometry --at maximum voluntary ventilation (LOINC)*.\n\n### By context\n\n- Resting, exercise, peri-procedure and peri-sedation variants: *3010647 / 9303-9 — --resting*, *3038563 / 40441-8 — --post exercise*, *36305182 / 89274-5 — --W exercise*, *36305857 / 89279-4 — --during anesthesia*, *3022705 / 19842-4 — --at maximum voluntary ventilation*, plus pre/post inhalation therapy, cardioversion, conscious sedation and bronchoscopy variants (LOINC).\n\n**Note on units**: reported in **/min** (`8541 / /min — per minute`, UCUM), the recommended unit (breaths per minute).\n\n## Mapping Notes\n\n- **Default concept** when the source records a respiratory rate without qualification: *3024171 / 9279-1 — Respiratory rate* (or SNOMED *4313591 / 86290005*).\n- **Measurement method / context / setting are attributes, not separate variables**: map to a method/context/setting concept only when the source documents it; otherwise use the generic concept. The ventilator set rate maps to *3007469 / 19834-1*.\n- This single set replaces the former separate ventilation-parameters respiratory-rate set (now deprecated).\n"
      },
      "fr": {
        "name": "Fréquence respiratoire (FR)",
        "category": "Paramètres vitaux",
        "subcategory": "Ventilatoire",
        "shortDescription": "Fréquence respiratoire (FR) — cycles par minute (/min) ; la fréquence mesurée (toute méthode, y compris au ventilateur) et la fréquence réglée du ventilateur.",
        "longDescription": null
      }
